Peer-assessment involves students' peers assessing their work. Written evaluations, rubrics, and spoken comments may be used for this. Peer-assessment may be utilized in classrooms, group projects, and online learning. Peer-assessment may benefit: Active learning and participation offering pupils feedback letting students appraise one other's work more objectively and accurately than teachers can. Teaching pupils critical thinking and evaluation Differentiating student work Student ownership and accountability for learning To achieve fair and accurate assessments, peer-assessment should be utilized as a supplement to teacher assessment and well-designed, executed, and monitored. It's also crucial to teach pupils how to perform courteous peer evaluations. 